<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>fly on the wall • let that fly stick to the wall</xh5><p> <i>fly on the wall—</i>an unperceived observer who is able to overhear discussions, etc.: “What did you wheedle out of Maggie?” “Well ... she was no <u>fly on the wall</u>, but there have to be letters, documents, papers to be typed.”</p><p> <i>let that fly stick to the wall</i>—(Scot.) say nothing more on that subject: We’ve got in our midst a newspaper; some people call it well, a very peculiar newspaper. But we’ll <u>let that fly stick to the wall</u>.</p> </entry>
